  "prompt": "What is a good inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center near Power County ID?",
  "response": "Finding a reputable inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center near Power County, Idaho, may require some research, as the area is relatively rural. Here are a few options that are within a reasonable driving distance or may offer transportation services:\n\n1. **Intermountain Hospital** (Boise, ID)  \n   Located about 2 hours from Power County, Intermountain Hospital offers comprehensive inpatient treatment for substance abuse and mental health disorders. They provide individualized care, detox services, and therapy programs.  \n   - Website: [Intermountain Hospital](https://intermountainhospital.com/)  \n\n2. **Idaho Behavioral Health** (Boise, ID)  \n   This facility offers a range of mental health and substance abuse treatment services, including inpatient programs. They focus on evidence-based treatment and holistic care.  \n   - Website: [Idaho Behavioral Health](https://idahobehavioralhealth.com/)  \n\n3. **Cascade Medical Center** (Cascade, ID)  \n   While not exclusively a rehab center, Cascade Medical Center provides resources and referrals for substance abuse treatment. They may help connect you with inpatient programs in the region.  \n\n4. **Blackfoot Guidance Center** (Blackfoot, ID)  \n   Located about an hour from Power County, this center offers outpatient and inpatient substance abuse services, including detox and counseling.  \n   - Website: [Blackfoot Guidance Center](https://blackfootguidancecenter.com/)  \n\n5. **Destinations To Recovery** (Caldwell, ID)  \n   This is a private rehab center offering intensive inpatient programs for drug and alcohol addiction. They focus on personalized care and long-term recovery.  \n   - Website: [Destinations To Recovery](https://destinationsrehab.com/)  \n\nWhen choosing a rehab center, consider factors such as the types of programs offered, accreditation, insurance acceptance, and reviews from past clients. It\u2019s also a good idea to contact the facilities directly to discuss your needs and confirm availability. If transportation is a concern, some centers offer assistance or can provide referrals to local resources.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
